args:
After hearing Chrom's story about the world's
destruction at Thórr's hands, Thórr herself
appears before the party. But the peril facing
the world grows all the more dire when
Empress Zethia appears as well.
Sheathe your sword, Prince Chrom.\nWe have no cause to fight.
I know you must have your reasons,\nbut I beg of you to share them with us!
Your sister has entrusted me with the\nfuture, Prince {player_name}.
I was bested and captured by Thórr and\nsent to a world very much like this one,\nyet also different.
It was a future version of this world—\none about to meet its ruin at Thórr's hand.
Wait, you were in OUR future?!
Other worlds are but other possibilities,\nand it would be no surprise to learn that\nour potential futures were among them.
In that world, I met Princess Zethia as\nshe battled Thórr's forces of destruction.
Princess Zethia, Thórr's host is nearly\nupon us. I fear the castle is unlikely\nto hold for much longer.
I am truly sorry to have involved an\noutsider like yourself in our tragedy,\nPrince Chrom.

You needn't apologize. While our birth
worlds may differ, our shared desire to
bring peace to our lands makes us kin
of another sort.

I will not abandon this world merely
because it is not my own. To do so
would make me unworthy to sit on
my own throne or any other.
Your fight this day is also my own.
But I fear the forces pouring through\nthe rift show no signs of diminishing.\nIt is only a matter of time until—
Has the attack begun?! Princess Zethia,\nI will halt Thórr's forces! Use that time\nto come up with some kind of plan!
Thórr! Your will has gone\nunchallenged long enough!
You may be called a god, but that does\nnot give you the right to trample upon\nthe lives of others!
You have quite the penchant for resisting\nfate, O prince of Ylisse.

But it makes no difference in the end.
This world has already been judged.
There is not a soul here worthy of
becoming a heavenly hero.
Now, feel the power of my divine hammer!
This is but an omen—a prelude to this\nworld's inevitable destruction.
Prepare yourselves.\nIt will be upon you soon.
Rrgh... DAMN HER!\nI need to check on the others...
Chrom, I... I have a favor to ask...
*cough* Please, don't trouble yourself.\nI know my time is running out.
We have a way to save this world now.\nI need you to take it back in time.
Yes. Go to the past, and prevent this future\nof despair from ever coming to fruition.
I understand if you find it hard to believe,\nbut I assure you, it IS the truth.
You are the root of that world's end.\nYour actions lead to its ruination.
That's a lie! He'd never do that!
I assure you, his intentions were pure.\nBut the righteousness and compassion\nof the prince still cause the world's doom.
And it all begins at this moment,\nwith the rescue of Prince Alfonse.
When you freed the captive Prince Alfonse,\nyou also unshackled his power.

Correct. Alas, this power caused the
world to become riddled with rifts—
a danger you likely understand
far better than myself.

I can think of numerous threats stemming
from such a thing: Rampaging fiends,
black mana floods, corruption from the
space between worlds...
So that's the reason you stopped us?
It was a reason, but not the only one.\nBecause the actual, direct cause of\nthe world's destruction...
Was Prince {player_name}\naccepting the power of the Other.
Fie, but this is madness! Never in all\nthe worlds would His Highness even\nTHINK to do such a thing!
To counteract an unworldly threat,\nhe sought an unworldly power.\nIs such a thing truly so strange?
Do you find my story plausible, Prince?\nAnd if so, do you still have the confidence\nyou can overcome the allure of power?
There is no shame in desiring power—\nespecially when you have devoted your\nlife to fighting on the faintest of hopes.
So you're the god of war who's\ntrying to destroy my world!
Do not mistake me, O dragonblood prince.
The destruction of worlds—or of men—\nis but the most trifling of matters to a god.\nWe neither seek it nor seek to prevent it.
But the souls of those who fight based\non the thinnest of hopes are a beautiful\nthing, and worthy of admiration.
You seek to doom their world only\nas a test to see if they can stop it!
You may interpret my words however\nit pleases you, humans.
Well, she's certainly arrogant\nenough to be a god...
I mean no disrespect. In fact, I have a\nrather great admiration for humanity.\nNow...show me your true strength!
No matter what you may say, Thórr,\nthere is no fate you can foist upon us\nthat I cannot change!
I told you before I was tired of you\ndoing whatever you pleased, and I'm\ngoing to stop it no matter what!
Chrom told us your plans, which means all\nwe need to do is leave my brother in your\ncaptivity for the time being!
Oh, I am under no obligation to wait for\nyou to free your beloved brother...
They're opening all over the dang place!\nWhat are we gonna do?!
I fear I will bring about the end of your\nworld, Prince {player_name}...
I sense it... The power is...\nAAAARRRGH!
Black mana is flowing out of\nPrince Alfonse's body!

The force which you call black mana has
amplified his gateway-opening powers
to an exponential degree. There is no
means within your power to stop it.
The wheel of fate has already begun\nto turn toward this world's end.
Well, isn't this just the most\nINTERESTING little chit-chat!

I see you just plopped yourself down in my
world and made yourself at home, mmm?
Guess I should have expected nothing
less from a ＂god.＂
Princess Zethia! ...But wait, no. \nI sense a...wrongness about her.
Yeeeaaah, it's Zethia, but also kinda not?\nSee, she sorta got possessed by an evil\nentity and... Look, it's a long story.
What is your business here, demon?
Was I not clear? I'm here to stop you\nfrom running roughshod over my world.
Interesting. I would think one such as\nyourself would delight in the destruction\nof the world.
By your hand? No. Now, if I'M the one\ndoing the destructing... Well then,\nthat's a very different story.
I see. Well, as I have no such preference\nin the matter, allow me to entrust this\nvessel to you.

Now THESE are the manners I expect
of a guest! I shall accept your offering—
goodness knows I've certainly received
worse gifts in my time.
Hey! You can't just pass around\npeople's brothers like that!
If the idea displeases you, claim him for\nyourself. He's right in front of you, yes?
Oh, I wasn't waiting for your permission!
We're taking Alfonse back,\nas well as my sister's body!

Don't be in such a hurry, dear brother.
Try to relax and just...enjoy the moment.
After all, it's not every day you get to
witness the world's end!
